text: Nash is a census-designated place and unincorporated community in Walsh County, North Dakota, United States. The population was 13 at the 2020 census. It was founded in 1890. Nash is located at (48.470556, -97.513056). == References == Category:1890s establishments in North Dakota Category:1890 establishments in the United States Category:Census-designated places in North Dakota Category:Unincorporated communities in North Dakota
